                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 28, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Adee directs Mr. Conger to consult General Chaffee with a view to
                    ascertaining, if possible, the fate of Americans at Paoting, reports regarding
                    which are conflicting; and, if any are alive, to report, dating his telegram, if
                    relief can be given.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
